body:
It should never exit `block_` with `S.in_directives = true`. Even if the block contains nothing but directives, when the closing brace is encountered the flag will be unset on [L713](https://github.com/mal/UglifyJS/blob/5ae3187cdb139015ef727a5a86d6d1dd216c6d1a/lib/parse-js.js#L713).

Running it over the code below gives the expected result in both the AST and mangled output. :)

``` js
function a(){
    "I am an important directive";
    function b(){
        "I'm a directive too";
    }
    "I am but a lowly string";
}
"just a string, doing my thing";
```

